Problem: Koko Eating Bananas (LeetCode 875)

Koko has several piles of bananas. The number of bananas in each pile is given in the array.

Koko can eat bananas at a speed of k bananas per hour.
If a pile has more bananas than k, she eats k bananas and continues in the next hour.
If a pile has less than k, she finishes that pile in one hour.

Goal:
Find the minimum eating speed (k) so that Koko can finish all the bananas within h hours.

Idea:
We use Binary Search on the eating speed.

Possible speed range:
Minimum speed = 1 banana per hour
Maximum speed = max element in piles (largest pile)

Steps:

1. Start Binary Search between 1 and the maximum pile size.
2. Pick the middle speed (mid).
3. Check how many hours Koko needs if she eats at speed mid.

To calculate hours:
For each pile:
hours = ceil(pile / mid)

If total hours ≤ h:
This speed works, but we try a smaller speed to minimize it.

If total hours > h:
This speed is too slow, so we increase the speed.

We continue the search until we find the minimum speed that allows Koko to finish within h hours.

Finally, return that minimum speed.

class Solution {
    public boolean isMin(int[] piles, int h, int mid) {
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < piles.length; i++) {
            count += piles[i] / mid;
            if (piles[i] % mid != 0) {
                count++;
            }
            if (count > h) {
                return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }

    public int minEatingSpeed(int[] piles, int h) {
        int n = piles.length;
        int ans = 0;
        int st = 1;
        int end = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            end = Math.max(end, piles[i]);
        }
        while (st <= end) {
            int mid = st + (end - st) / 2;

            if (isMin(piles, h, mid)) {
                ans = mid;
                end = mid - 1;
            } else {
                st = mid + 1;
            }
        }

        return ans;

    }
}

Time Complexity: O(n log m)
n = number of piles
m = maximum pile size

Space Complexity: O(1)
